{"ts":"2026-06-12T22:47:32.675Z","author":"audit-quality-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-bzgt"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Dedupe history-rewrite orchestration block triplicated across history-redact/repair/compact"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Follow-up to closed pm-kbm9 (PR#74), which dedup'd checkHistoryRewriteOwnership + verifyHistoryRewriteNoDrift as helpers but left the surrounding ~50-line orchestration triplicated: verifyHistoryChain error -> ownership warnings -> acquireLock(pmRoot, subject.id, ttl, author, force, force_required_for_stale_lock) -> verifyHistoryRewriteNoDrift -> writeFileAtomic(historyEntriesToRaw) with rollback -> release. Sites: src/cli/commands/history-redact.ts ~525-600, src/cli/commands/history-repair.ts ~165-240, src/cli/commands/history-compact.ts ~310-380. Extract an executeHistoryRewrite({operation, subject, rewrittenEntries, itemDocument, author, force, settings, typeRegistry, historyRawBeforeLock, currentItemRawBeforeLock, dryRun}) helper in src/core/history (next to replay.ts/history-rewrite helpers); each command keeps only its rewrite computation. Bonus: a small 100%-coverable core module per the coverage tactic."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Chore"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["audit-2026-06-13","dedup","history","refactor"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-12T22:47:32.675Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-12T22:47:32.675Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"audit-quality-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-y7sc"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"863afd3cf6af83ec0d4d155fb3fb5c7cf237e690644c84702980635cbac08d75","message":""}
